    <data key="d0">OpenFit Continuous Deployment Pipeline with ChatOps Approval</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kebb0LOVC28</data>
    <data key="d2">OpenFit uses a serverless-first approach for its digital streaming platform. This architecture focuses on their continuous deployment pipeline, emphasizing rapid deployments (3-4 times daily) and a chat ops model for approvals to avoid traditional bottlenecks. The system ensures immutable artifacts are built, stored, and deployed consistently across QA and production environments. A key design decision was to integrate interactive Slack messages for manual approval steps, allowing the DevOps team to control releases directly from their chat platform.</data>
    <data key="d3">data_ingestion, interactive, compute_intensive, control</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
</graphml>
